                            <comment id="13760998" author="fpj" created="Sat, 7 Sep 2013 12:25:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;A couple of comments about the patches:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I was thinking that the test case should check that the state of the zk handle is CONNECTEDREADONLY before shooting the operation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The list of requests to filter should be the same for trunk and 3.4, except for reconfig, so if one has check, I think the other one needs to have it too, and trunk has it. But, I don&apos;t really see a reason for filtering check. It will most likely come with another write request in the multi call which falls in the switch case.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
